definition: to flow/to disseminate/to circulate or spread/to move or drift/to degenerate/to banish or send into exile/stream of water or sth resembling one/class, rate or grade

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc

sentences.english: It is the heavy metals contained in the waste effluent that can cause an environmental or disposal problem.
sentences.chinese: 就是流出廢液中的重金屬能導致環境或處理問題。

sentences.english: The water then flows out of the side of the valley to form a spring.
sentences.chinese: 然後，水從山谷坡上流出，形成泉。

sentences.english: Water will come out of this tube and flow into the bowl.
sentences.chinese: 水會從這條管子流出，再留進碗裏。

sentences.english: it was true that the rescued cruel man let fuel oil issue from the tissue.
sentences.chinese: 得到挽救的無情鬚眉真的聽憑燃油從薄紗中流出。

sentences.english: The black rocks are all lava from a volcano which erupted here 10.000 years ago.
sentences.chinese: 這些黑色的岩石都是一萬年前火山爆發流出的岩漿。

sentences.english: Take a look at the excurrent canal of certain sponges.
sentences.chinese: 請看看若干海綿之流出管。

sentences.english: She looked at her son,her eyes leaking glad tears.
sentences.chinese: 她看着她的兒子，眼裏流出高興的眼淚。

sentences.english: So when we talk about failed surgery, it means no flow.
sentences.chinese: 因此，當我們說到手術失敗，即意味着房水不能流出。

sentences.english: The oil flowed over the rim of the drum.
sentences.chinese: 油從汽油桶的邊緣流出。

sentences.english: Fresh water runs from the spring.
sentences.chinese: 新鮮的水是從泉中流出的。

sentences.english: The words flowed unbidden from my pen.
sentences.chinese: 這些字句從我的筆端滾滾流出。

sentences.english: If the level is correct, fluid should just trickle, or drip out of, the centre of the drain plug.
sentences.chinese: 如果油量正確，你只會見到波箱油慢慢滴或者流出黎。

sentences.english: Warm wet plastic came out of the end of the pipe.
sentences.chinese: 管子的出口流出熱乎乎的液體塑料。

sentences.english: Just a cleansed channel For Thy life through me.
sentences.chinese: 作一潔淨器皿，流出袮生命。

sentences.english: She had a bottomless well of love for me.
sentences.chinese: 她有一座無底的井，對我源源不斷流出愛。

sentences.english: The water butt catches the overflow from this pipe.
sentences.chinese: 大水桶盛接管子裏流出的東西。

definition: to flow/to disseminate/to circulate or spread/to move or drift/to degenerate/to banish or send into exile/stream of water or sth resembling one/class, rate or grade
to gush/to gush out/to pour out
leading/in first place/top of the list
to overflow/(literary) excessive/old variant of 鎰|镒[yi4]
to leak out/to release (liquid or gas)
to flow back/reflux/circumfluence/refluence/backward flow/returning flow (e.g. of talent)
